HEADWORD: Patonce
<hw>Pa*tonce"</hw> <pr>(p⟦adot⟧*t⟦ocr⟧ns")</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
F. <ets>patte d'once</ets> paw of an ounce.]</ety> <fld>(Her.)</fld>
<def>Having the arms growing broader and floriated toward the end; --
said of a cross. See <xex>Illust.</xex> 9 of <er>Cross</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

